commText: Rahane and Gaikwad are at the crease. Rahane is on strike. Rabada will open the attack
Rabada to Rahane, wide, good length delivery that slides down leg first up, little loosener
Rabada to Rahane, 1 run, shade fuller and on the pads, clipped away easily to deep backward square leg
Rabada to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery on middle, gently bunted towards mid-on for a quick single, he's off the mark
Rabada to Rahane, 2 runs, full and on the stumps, Rahane clips it away through the gap at mid-wicket, not the best of timing and they'll get two
Rabada to Rahane, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, Rahane hangs back and eases it down to third man
Rabada to Gaikwad, no run, full and just outside off, Gaikwad prods forward to block and gets a thick inside edge onto the pads
Rabada to Gaikwad, no run, good length delivery just outside off, Gaikwad prods half forward to defend and gets a thick inside edge that goes back to hit his box, seems to be in a bit of pain
CSK have lost the toss in 10 of their 11 matches this season.
Most tosses lost in first 11 games of an IPL season 10 - RR in 2022 10 - CSK in 2024 9 - MI in 2011 9 - DC in 2013
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Arshdeep Singh to Rahane, FOUR, beautiful shot! Pitched up full on off-stump, Rahane pressed forward and creamed that straight back past his partner at the other end, didn't bother running even a couple of steps
Arshdeep Singh to Rahane, no run, beaten this time, pulls the length back just a touch and slants it across outside off, Rahane pushes at it again and is beaten
Arshdeep Singh to Rahane, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tucked away towards deep backward square leg, just one
Arshdeep Singh to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, Gaikwad bunts it towards mid-off and takes him on for a quick single, makes it comfortably
Umpire review. PBKS are claiming a catch but Rahane thinks it's a bump-ball
Arshdeep Singh to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Rahane, out Caught by Rabada!! That's gone straight off the bat and straight to the man! Rahane will have to walk back. Pitched right up, yorker length and on middle, Rahane looked to flick it into the leg-side and lost his balance, he hit it straight to the man at mid-wicket. It went quick and low and Rahane thought it was a bump ball but it went straight to Rabada at mid-wicket. Another failure for the veteran and Punjab draw first blood. Rahane c Rabada b Arshdeep Singh 9(7) [4s-1]
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tucked into the leg-side towards mid-wicket for one

Rabada to Mitchell, 3 runs, length delivery outside off, flayed away over cover, was struck on the up and he didn't time it, got it over the infield and it was chased down, seems like a fairly slow outfield
Rabada to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery outside off, eased down to third man
Rabada to Mitchell, 1 run, very full and on the stumps, flicked away to deep square leg
Rabada to Gaikwad, FOUR, nicely struck! Pitched up full and on the pads, Gaikwad whipped it away in the air and got it over mid-wicket, vast spaces there in the outfield
Rabada to Gaikwad, no run, good length delivery on leg-stump, follows him as he backs away and Gaikwad knocks it into the covers
Rabada to Gaikwad, no run, back of a length outside off, good bounce there and Gaikwad was beaten as he hung his bat out at it

Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell, FOUR, into the gap! Back of a length outside off, Mitchell was very quick on to the backfoot before pulling that away into a fairly small gap at mid-wicket, rolled his wrists and kept it down

Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell, SIX, that's a glorious shot! Good length delivery slanting across outside off, Mitchell just planted his foot forward and lofted it on the up and through the line, hit it well enough to take it over the long-off ropes
Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell, no run, full and on the middle, driven straight to mid-on
Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell, no run, very full on off-stump, knocked into the covers
Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell, 1 run, banged in short on middle, Mitchell got on top of the bounce and pulled it powerfully to the right of the man at deep square leg, he did well to stop that
Arshdeep Singh to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, eased out towards cover for a single
Sam Curran, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Sam Curran to Gaikwad, 1 run, length delivery on middle, clipped away to deep square leg
Sam Curran to Mitchell, 2 runs, full and on the pads, fliicked away in front of square on the leg-side, couple more taken
Sam Curran going round the wicket now
Sam Curran to Mitchell, 1 run, fired in full on off-stump, Mitchell makes a lot of room and carves it out towards cover for a quick single
Sam Curran to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, Gaikwad hangs back and punches it straight to point for a quick single
Sam Curran to Mitchell, 2 runs, good length delivery on middle, tucked away gently towards deep mid-wicket and they charge back for two, good running
Sam Curran to Mitchell, no run, good length delivery on middle, Mitchell backed away to make some room and punched it straight to mid-off, was in the air but didn't carry to the fielder
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Gaikwad, no run, full on leg-stump, followed him as Gaikwad made room, carved to cover in the end
Harpreet Brar to Gaikwad, SIX, superb strike! Full on middle-leg, Gaikwad stepped out and got to the pitch of it before lofting it clean over the long-on ropes, excellent use of the feet
Harpreet Brar to Gaikwad, FOUR, width on offer and slapped! Harpreet Brar looked to correct, went flat and outside off, Gaikwad was waiting for just that as he slapped it away hard through cover

Harpreet Brar to Gaikwad, FOUR, back to back fours! Floated up full on leg-stump, Gaikwad backed away a long way to make room before carving it up and over extra cover, no one out there in the deep on the off-side
Harpreet Brar to Gaikwad, 1 run, full on off-stump, pushed down the ground to long off

Harpreet Brar to Mitchell, FOUR, that'll run away too! Full on middle, Mitchell ran down the track looking to go big down the ground, he got a thick inside edge and it raced away through the gap between short fine-leg and backward square leg, big over that - 19 off it

Powerplay summary -- CSK off to a brisk start -- Arshdeep gets rid of Rahane for 9 (1.5) -- Mitchell starts in an aggressive manner -- Gaikwad cuts loose in final over of powerplay -- Brar goes for 19 in his first over

Sam Curran to Gaikwad, FOUR, that's the 50-run stand up! Just back of a length and angling into the batter on middle, Gaikwad hung back and short-arm jabbed it towards deep mid-wicket, went over the man who was a few paces in and just landed inside the ropes
Sam Curran to Gaikwad, 1 run, full outside off, driven down the ground to long-off
Sam Curran to Mitchell, 1 run, full outside off, pushed down the ground to long off
Sam Curran to Gaikwad, 1 run, full and straight on middle, whipped away to deep mid-wicket, they thought of two but the fielder got to it very quickly

Sam Curran to Mitchell, 1 run, will go down as a drop! Slower delivery full outside off, Mitchell absolutely clubbed that back, went quick to Curran's left and he stuck his hand out, no real chance of taking that, hit his fingertips really hard and went down to long-off
Sam Curran to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length delivery angling into off-stump, Gaikwad presses back and eases it towards short third man for a quick single
Timeout. A better powerplay for CSK this time round. They didn't let Brar settle into things this time around, heads-up play from Gaikwad to attack him straightaway.
Rahul Chahar, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rahul Chahar to Gaikwad, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! A wicket right after the break! Length delivery wide outside off, was a poor delivery and Gaikwad was looking to dispatch that to the ropes. It probably just bounced a bit more than he expected and he got a healthy edge through to the keeper. Big wicket for PBKS, the CSK skipper and man in form is on his way back. Gaikwad c Jitesh Sharma b Rahul Chahar 32(21) [4s-4 6s-1]
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rahul Chahar to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rahul Chahar to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! He's got two in two! Dube is out for a golden duck for the second time in a row! Flatter and quicker, was the wrong-un that was pushed across outside off and Shivam Dube hung back looking to cut that away, he went at it with an angled bat though and got a healthy outside edge. He's out in almost the same fashion as his skipper and is gone without troubling the scorers once more! Oh dear, CSK in a spot of bother now. Shivam Dube c Jitesh Sharma b Rahul Chahar 0(1)
Rahul Chahar is on a hat-trick now!
Moeen Ali, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rahul Chahar to Moeen Ali, no run, hat-trick is kept out safely, flat and quick just outside off, Moeen Ali pushes it straight back to the bowler
Rahul Chahar to Moeen Ali, no run, tossed up full on off-stump, Moeen Ali leans in to defend and gets a thick inside edge onto the pads

Rahul Chahar to Moeen Ali, 1 run, oh just out of his reach! Length delivery on off-stump, another wrong-un and Moeen Ali hit it right off the toe end as he looked to push it down to long-on, wasn't too far away from Chahar's outstretched left hand
Rahul Chahar to Mitchell, 1 run, length delivery on middle, Mitchell reverse-sweeps it towards backward point and they steal a quick single, direct-hit and it would've been tight
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Mitchell, 1 run, full and on the pads, clipped away to deep mid-wicket
Harshal Patel to Moeen Ali, 1 run, very full and wide outside off from round the wicket, squeezed out to third man
Harshal Patel to Mitchell, 1 run, full and outside off, knocked down to long-off
Harshal Patel to Moeen Ali, 1 run, full outside off, driven out square to deep point
CSK review. Mitchell has been given out lbw and he wants another look
Harshal Patel to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Harshal Patel to Mitchell, out Lbw!! That's a bit of a shocker to get! Length delivery outside off, angled back in and kept surprisingly low, nipped back enough to go past the inside edge and hit his front pad as he looked to tuck it into the leg-side. UltraEdge shows that it would've just gone on to clip leg-stump! It will remain out on umpire's call and Mitchell looks very very unhappy as he walks off. Another big blow for CSK, they've lost 4 wickets inside 10 overs here. Mitchell lbw b Harshal Patel 30(19) [4s-2 6s-1]
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Jadeja, wide, good length delivery going well down leg from round the wicket
Harshal Patel to Jadeja, no run, full just outside off, driven straight to mid-off
Rahul Chahar to Moeen Ali, no run, tossed up full on off-stump, pushed straight back to the bowler
Rahul Chahar to Moeen Ali, 1 run, very full on middle, driven straight back and Rahul Chahar ends up deflecting it towards mid-off
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, 1 run, tossed up full on middle, Jadeja leans in and sweeps it away towards deep square leg, looked like he wanted to go a lot straighter
Rahul Chahar to Moeen Ali, 1 run, full on middle-leg, Moeen Ali looks to work it into the leg-side and gets a leading edge that goes towards point
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, no run, flatter delivery on off-stump, Jadeja hangs back and blocks
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, no run, floated up full on middle, Jadeja presses forward and knocks it back to the bowler's right
Harshal Patel to Moeen Ali, no run, full on off-stump, driven straight to mid-off
Harshal Patel to Moeen Ali, 1 run, very full and outside off, carved out to third man

Harshal Patel to Jadeja, 1 run, just short of long-on! Full on middle, Jadeja took a step down the track and looked to loft it down the ground, didn't time it and the bat turned in his hand, he just checked his shot and maybe that's what saves him
Harshal Patel to Moeen Ali, 1 run, length delivery outside off, Moeen Ali runs it down fine to third man

Harshal Patel to Jadeja, FOUR, mid-off was up and he takes him on! Full and just outside off, this is what he wanted to to earlier in the over, he drove it up and through the line, didn't time it well again but got enough to go over mid-off and take it to the boundary

Harshal Patel to Jadeja, FOUR, mis-field and it runs away! Length delivery outside off, Jadeja waited for it and cut it away, hit it straight to backward point and the fielder let it through his legs, not a great effort
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Moeen Ali, no run, full on the pads, clipped straight to mid-wicket
Rabada to Moeen Ali, no run, slower length delivery slanting across just outside off, Moeen Ali looks to punch it through the off-side and is beaten
Rabada to Moeen Ali, FOUR, full-toss and put away! Friendly full-toss on off-stump, Moeen Ali just picked it up and whipped it over mid-wicket, vast open spaces there and he gets four
Rabada to Moeen Ali, no run, short of length and just outside off, Moeen Ali looks to pull it away and misses, beaten for pace there

Rabada to Moeen Ali, FOUR, he finds the gap again! Length delivery outside off, Moeen Ali hung back and used the pace to punch it towards backward point, the man there and got his hand to it before couldn't take enough pace off to stop it
Rabada to Moeen Ali, 1 run, length delivery outside off, eased down to third man
Sam Curran [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Moeen Ali, no run, full outside off, driven straight to extra cover
Sam Curran to Moeen Ali, 1 run, slower delivery full on off-stump, hacked away towards cow corner
Sam Curran to Jadeja, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, pace off again, Jadeja bunted it into the off-side and they scurried through for a quick single as it went towards point
Sam Curran to Moeen Ali, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sam Curran to Moeen Ali, out Caught by Bairstow!! Here's another wicket! Moeen was struggling to time it and he's gone now. Banged in short on off-stump, pace off again and Moeen Ali looked to pull it away, it got big on him and took the top-edge before settling neatly into Bairstow's hands at short fine-leg. The slide continues for CSK. Moeen Ali c Bairstow b Sam Curran 17(20) [4s-2]
Mitchell Santner, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Sam Curran to Santner, 1 run, length delivery outside off, punched out towards deep point
Sam Curran to Jadeja, 1 run, slower length delivery outside off, cut away to deep point
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Jadeja, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full on off, Jadeja gets forward to drive to long-off
Harshal Patel to Santner, 1 run, good stop by Ashutosh at short fine-leg, moving to his right, Curran claps to applaud that effort, tucked and was going at pace
Harshal Patel to Jadeja, no run, well stopped. A slower ball full on off, drilled back and Harshal Patel got down quickly to stop
Harshal Patel to Jadeja, 3 runs, slower ball full outside off, driven nicely and long chase for Arshdeep from sweeper cover and by the time he gets across and cuts it off, they take three
Harshal Patel to Santner, no run, slow short ball on the stumps, Santner bends his head to leave, he has a wry smile on his face
Harshal Patel to Santner, 1 run, slower ball full outside off, Santner drives hard and straight to long-off
Devon Conway is in the audience. Watching on.
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Santner, no run, good length and tight on the stumps, defended back
Arshdeep Singh to Santner, FOUR, short of length and sliding down leg, helped away wide of backward square leg, flies away, bad ball and put away
Arshdeep Singh to Santner, 1 run, back of a length on the stumps, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, 1 run, full on the stumps, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Santner, 1 run, slower ball on a length outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, 1 run, slower short ball on the stumps, Jadeja waits and pulls to deep backward square leg
Timeout! CSK are content in taking the singles at the moment. No boundaries and PBKS are very happy. CSK need at least 175 to fight on this.

Highlights (Overs 7-15) -- 57/4, 6.33rpo -- CSK lose their way after powerplay -- Chahar takes two wickets in two balls -- Gaikwad caught-behind off Chahar for 32 (7.1) -- Dube goes for a golden duck again (7.2) -- Mitchell trapped LBW by Harshal for 30 (8.5) -- Curran gets rid of Moeen for 17 (12.4)
Rahul Chahar [2.0-0-5-2] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, 1 run, fraction short and turning in to off, Jadeja pulls to deep mid-wicket
Rahul Chahar to Santner, 1 run, tossed up on off, Santner with a forward defence wide of extra-cover
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, 1 run, short and wide outside off, cut wide of extra-cover and Harpreet dives to his right to save three
Rahul Chahar to Santner, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Santner drags the slogsweep to deep square leg
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, 1 run, flat good length on leg-stump, tucked to deep square leg
Rahul Chahar to Santner, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rahul Chahar to Santner, out Caught by Sam Curran!! Straight to long-on. Just 5 off the over and Santner wanted to get a biggie, tossed up googly outside off, Santner fetches the loft and does not get enough to clear Curran on the edge of the ropes. Santner c Sam Curran b Rahul Chahar 11(11) [4s-1]
Shardul Thakur, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Sam Curran [3.0-0-20-1] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Jadeja, 1 run, full on the stumps, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Sam Curran to Thakur, FOUR, beautiful straight drive. Full on the stumps, Thakur holds his balance and thumps the drive straight down the ground

Sam Curran to Thakur, SIX, dropped by Shashank Singh at deep mid-wicket. He was running back and he has tipped it over the cushions. Sam Curran is not happy, shakes his head, full on the stumps, whipped and Shashank was in from the fence, to prevent the two, made a meal of it
Sam Curran to Thakur, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, whipped and no timing this time, lands well short of Shashank at deep mid-wicket
Sam Curran to Jadeja, 1 run, back of the hand slower ball which is delivered with a leg-cut, short, Jadeja pulls to deep square leg
Can't understand Jadeja's strategy here. He is not even trying to go for the big hits. Happy to nudge and nurdle around. Bizarre!
Sam Curran to Thakur, 1 run, full outside off, dragged drive to long-on
Rahul Chahar to Thakur, FOUR, fine shot. A flat legbreak outside off, on a good length, Thakur smashes it on the rise, flat hit over extra-cover
Rahul Chahar to Thakur, 1 run, good length and on leg-stump, swiped to deep square leg

Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, SIX, looks like Jadeja has woken up! This is the tossed up googly outside off, he gets low and slogsweeps it way over deep mid-wicket, sailed away, heaves a sigh of relief after hitting that
Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, 1 run, a dart on a back of a length on the stumps, Jadeja pulls to deep mid-wicket
Rahul Chahar coming diagonally now to Thakur.
Rahul Chahar to Thakur, wide, way outside off, left alone and wide taken
Rahul Chahar to Thakur, no run, flat legbreak outside off, turns and beats Thakur's heave

Rahul Chahar to Thakur, no run, another swing and a miss, similar delivery to the last one, Thakur can't connect, Jitesh Sharma has the bails off but the back foot is firmly grounded behind the crease
Harshal Patel [3.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Jadeja, 1 run, full and following Jadeja outside the leg-stump as he comes down the track, driven to long-on
Harshal Patel to Thakur, no run, fine slower ball off-cutter that dips on Thakur just outside off, who swings and misses, a fumble from Jitesh Sharma but Jadeja is sent back
And shouts of "Dhoni" echo around the ground. For that one of these two have to get out. Don't rule it out though.
Harshal Patel to Thakur, no run, four balls Thakur has not laid bat on. Another slower ball off-cutter that dips near the yorker length, outside off, Thakur can't connect
Harshal Patel to Thakur, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Harshal Patel to Thakur, out Bowled!! Cleaned up. Thakur does something different, gives the charge but the slower ball off-cutter dips under the bat and crashes into the stumps. Fine bowling and Thakur had no clue. Thakur b Harshal Patel 17(11) [4s-2 6s-1]

And right on cue, out walks Dhoni - in the 19th over. Cleverly kept himself back even when wickets were falling today. Sent Santner and Thakur ahead of him. Now is in hoping to maximise the last 8 balls. Can he do so? The crowd which has a fair bit of yellow, breaks into chants of "Dhoni" multiple times. What can he come up with to please them?
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Dhoni, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Harshal Patel to Dhoni, out Bowled!! The yellow army has been silenced by Harshal Patel who has his arms aloft in celebration. The Dhoni army cover their faces in horror. Their hero is gone for a golden duck. Today the strategy to come at the end has not paid off. Another superb slower ball off-cutter on the stumps, dips on Dhoni who like Thakur has no clue, tries to bring his bat down but the ball dips and goes past the weak swipe to leg, the off-stump is pegged back and there begins traumatic scenes for the Dhoni army. PBKS' fans though love it with Preity Zinta breaking into a big blushing smile. Dhoni while walking back, nodded at Jadeja - perhaps suggesting he was totally deceived. Dhoni b Harshal Patel 0(1)
Tushar Deshpande, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Tushar Deshpande, wide, way outside off, full and the hat-trick ball is a wide
Harshal Patel to Tushar Deshpande, no run, full on the stumps, drilled straight to the fielder at mid-off
Arshdeep Singh [3.0-0-27-1] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, FOUR, low full-toss on the stumps swung away to the deep backward square leg fence, good hit but Jadeja is not happy, wanted more
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, 2 runs, slower short of length delivery outside off, flat-batted wide of long-off and Jadeja gets back for two
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, wide, just wide of the tramline on the off-side, full and left alone to take the wide
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, SIX, this is a poor ball. Full and in the slot outside off, Jadeja lofts over wide long-on, gets forward and goes big, all the way
Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Jadeja, out Caught by Sam Curran!! Into the wicket works. Off-pace knuckle short ball outside off, Jadeja miscues the pull and an easy catch for long-on. Curran never dropping that. Jadeja c Sam Curran b Arshdeep Singh 43(26) [4s-3 6s-2]
Richard Gleeson, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Arshdeep Singh to Richard Gleeson, 2 runs, the attempted yorker from round the wicket is a low full-toss, pushed to long-off and confusion between the two for the second but Tushar Deshpande gets back, a direct-hit at his end would still have been interesting
Arshdeep Singh to Richard Gleeson, leg byes, 1 run, short of length and angling into the pads, Richard Gleeson pulls and misses, off the pad for a legbye

17:16 Local Time, 11:46 GMT, 17:16 IST: CSK end on 167. It's not a great total on this wicket. Rahane went early but Gaikwad and Mitchell looked good in their 2nd wicket stand but enter Rahul Chahar who took 2 in 2 after the first timeout. That included another golden duck for Dube and the innings needed consolidating. Moeen and Jadeja added a little stand after Mitchell was trapped LBW. Mo did not make it big and wickets continued to fall. CSK must have considered Sameer Rizvi as the impact sub when wickets were falling but instead they sent Santer and Thakur ahead of Dhoni who again was kept back for the last two overs. Rahul Chahar came back and bowled another couple of good overs at the death while Harshal bowled an exceptional 19th over which included 2 in 2, getting Thakur and Dhoni off successive balls. No party today for the men in yellow who turned up to see another Dhoni special. The last over saw Jadeja hit a four and a six before he fell. 167 on this looks at least 20 short. What can CSK conjure up with the ball? Back for the reply in 5 minutes...
Rahul Chahar vs CSK Matches: 13 Wickets: 15 Avg: 20.06 SR: 19.6 ER: 6.14 BBI: 3/23
Ravindra Jadeja vs Rahul Chahar in the IPL Runs: 29 Balls: 33 Dismissals: 1 SR: 87.87 Dots: 14
Today was the first time MS Dhoni batted at No.9 or lower in his T20 career. His eight innings at No.8 have all come across IPL 2023 and 2024.
MS Dhoni vs Harshal Patel in the IPL Runs: 25 Balls: 33 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 8.33 SR: 75.75 4s/6s: 2/0 Dots: 16
CSK innings progression Overs 1-7: 69/1 (RR: 9.85) Overs 8-16: 53/5 (RR: 5.88) Overs 17-20: 45/3 (RR: 11.25)
PBKS bowling \nRahul Chahar & Harshal Patel: 6/47 from 8 overs (ER: 5.875) \nOthers: 3/119 from 12 overs (ER: 9.91)

Harshal: Wicket was on drier side. I have too much respect for him to celebrate when I get him out (on Dhoni). One of the advantages of playing a day game is that the square is quite rough. So the ball starts reversing. In my first over it was reversing. It's all about the feel of that delivery (slower one). More you bowl the better you get. Most batters don't pick it. Have been practicing in the nets, and when it comes out it gives you great results.
Welcome back. PBKS have their impact sub - Prabhsimran in, Arshdeep out. CSK too have theirs - Simarjeet in for Rahane. Santner from round the wicket.
